The assignment is to support the Dam Rehabilitation and Improvement Project (DRIP) in India, whose exact site is not specified in the provided documents (the “Location of Overall assignment” field is left blank) [Tendernotice_1.pdf, p:11](chunkref://12).  

**Project objectives** – The consultant must   
* develop and improve a standard project‑template form and a web‑based Management Information System (MIS) to capture technical, environmental, social and implementation data for each dam [Tendernotice_1.pdf, p:20](chunkref://24);  
* provide technical, managerial and troubleshooting support to State Project Management Units (SPMUs) and implementing agencies, including detailed site inspections, environmental assessments and preparation of asset‑management plans [Tendernotice_1.pdf, p:20](chunkref://24);  
* guide procurement in line with World Bank guidelines and assist SPMUs on procurement matters [Tendernotice_1.pdf, p:20](chunkref://24);  
* produce a suite of reports and guidelines (e.g., quarterly/annual financial reports, project implementation reports, ICRR, dam‑safety guidelines, dam design‑review manual) [Tendernotice_1.pdf, p:37](chunkref://62);  
* develop the DHARMA software and related system‑requirement studies [Tendernotice_1.pdf, p:37](chunkref://62).  

**Specialness and potential difficulties** – The work involves   
* complex dam rehabilitation cases that may require “detailed site inspection” and preparation of site‑specific environmental assessments and EMPs [Tendernotice_1.pdf, p:20](chunkref://24);  
* coordination across multiple agencies (SPMUs, World Bank, CWC) and integration of diverse data streams (technical, social, environmental, financial) [Tendernotice_1.pdf, p:20](chunkref://24);  
* adherence to stringent World Bank procurement and reporting standards [Tendernotice_1.pdf, p:20](chunkref://24).  

**Innovative solutions** – The scope explicitly calls for the design and customization of new software tools (web‑MIS, DHARMA) and the creation of novel guidelines and manuals, indicating a need for innovative, possibly proprietary, solutions [Tendernotice_1.pdf, p:37](chunkref://62).  

**Interdisciplinary expertise** – The tasks span technical dam engineering, environmental and social impact assessment, financial management, procurement, and information‑technology development, confirming that interdisciplinary expertise is required [Tendernotice_1.pdf, p:20](chunkref://24); [Tendernotice_1.pdf, p:37](chunkref://62).  

**Software, tools, or proprietary methodologies** – The tenderer must deliver   
* a web‑based MIS, * the DHARMA software, * customized financial‑reporting software, * document‑management and dissemination systems, and * various templates and guidelines [Tendernotice_1.pdf, p:37](chunkref://62); these are core deliverables, so the consultant is expected to provide the necessary software and tools (including any proprietary methodologies).  

**Limitations** – The precise geographic location of the project is not provided in the excerpts, so that detail cannot be confirmed from the current context.
